"Henley-on-Thames, Oxfordshire, England","St Helen Bishopsgate, London, England, United Kingdom":"St Helen Bishopsgate, London, England, United Kingdom","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England","North Mymms, Hertfordshire, England":"North Mymms, Hertfordshire, England"},"nl":{"1481–1521":"1481–1521","1478–1527":"1478–1527","1479–1501":"1479–1501","1485–1558":"1485–1558","1514–1596":"1514–1596","1449–Male":"1449–Overleden","–Female":"Overleden","9 July 1514":"9 juli 1514","15 November 1509":"15 november 1509","1481":"1481","13 November 1520":"13 november 1520","1514":"1514","1558":"1558","1501":"1501","1479":"1479","1500":"1500","1478":"1478","1488":"1488","1521":"1521","1596":"1596","1485":"1485","1527":"1527","1449":"1449","Henley-on-Thames, Oxfordshire, England":"Henley-on-Thames, Oxfordshire, England","St Helen Bishopsgate, London, England, United Kingdom":"St Helen Bishopsgate, London, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England","North Mymms, Hertfordshire, England":"North Mymms, Hertfordshire, England"},"en":{"1481–1521":"1481–1521","1478–1527":"1478–1527","1479–1501":"1479–1501","1485–1558":"1485–1558","1514–1596":"1514–1596","1449–Male":"1449–Deceased","–Female":"Deceased","9 July 1514":"9 July 1514","15 November 1509":"15 November 1509","1481":"1481","13 November 1520":"13 November 1520","1514":"1514","1558":"1558","1501":"1501","1479":"1479","1500":"1500","1478":"1478","1488":"1488","1521":"1521","1596":"1596","1485":"1485","1527":"1527","1449":"1449","Henley-on-Thames, Oxfordshire, England":"Henley-on-Thames, Oxfordshire, England","St Helen Bishopsgate, London, England, United Kingdom":"St Helen Bishopsgate, London, England, United Kingdom","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England","North Mymms, Hertfordshire, England":"North Mymms, Hertfordshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Knollys","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Knowles  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Knowles","meanings":["English: topographic name from Middle English <i>knol(le)</i> ‘knoll, hilltop’ (Old English <i>cnoll</i>) or from any of the many places (some lost) named with this word, for example Knowle (Devon, Dorset, Lancashire, Somerset, Warwickshire, and Yorkshire) and Knole (Kent, Sussex).","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Tnúthghail</b> (see   Newell  ).","English: variant of   Noel  , often, with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Sir Robert Knollys was born in 1481, in North Mymms, Hertfordshire, England as the son of Robert Knollys and Elizabeth Troutbeck. He had at least 1 son with Lettice Peniston. In 1509, at the age of 28, his occupation is listed as he continued in the same office under henry viii, and received an annuity of £20, on 15 november 1509, and a grant of upclatford, called rookes manor, in hampshire — part of the confiscated property of sir richard empson — on 10 february 1510/11. . He died in 1521, in Henley-on-Thames, Oxfordshire, England, at the age of 40, and was buried in St Helen Bishopsgate, London, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1481–1521":"1481–1521","1478–1527":"1478–1527","1479–1501":"1479–1501","1485–1558":"1485–1558","1514–1596":"1514–1596","1449–Male":"1449–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","9 July 1514":"9. juuli 1514","15 November 1509":"15. november 1509","1481":"1481","13 November 1520":"13. november 1520","1514":"1514","1558":"1558","1501":"1501","1479":"1479","1500":"1500","1478":"1478","1488":"1488","1521":"1521","1596":"1596","1485":"1485","1527":"1527","1449":"1449","Henley-on-Thames, Oxfordshire, England":"Henley-on-Thames, Oxfordshire, England","St Helen Bishopsgate, London, England, United Kingdom":"St Helen Bishopsgate, London, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England","North Mymms, Hertfordshire, England":"North Mymms, Hertfordshire, England"},"fi":{"1481–1521":"1481–1521","1478–1527":"1478–1527","1479–1501":"1479–1501","1485–1558":"1485–1558","1514–1596":"1514–1596","1449–Male":"1449–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","9 July 1514":"9. heinäkuuta 1514","15 November 1509":"15. marraskuuta 1509","1481":"1481","13 November 1520":"13. marraskuuta 1520","1514":"1514","1558":"1558","1501":"1501","1479":"1479","1500":"1500","1478":"1478","1488":"1488","1521":"1521","1596":"1596","1485":"1485","1527":"1527","1449":"1449","Henley-on-Thames, Oxfordshire, England":"Henley-on-Thames, Oxfordshire, England","St Helen Bishopsgate, London, England, United Kingdom":"St Helen Bishopsgate, London, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England","North Mymms, Hertfordshire, England":"North Mymms, Hertfordshire, England"},"fr":{"1481–1521":"1481–1521","1478–1527":"1478–1527","1479–1501":"1479–1501","1485–1558":"1485–1558","1514–1596":"1514–1596","1449–Male":"1449–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","9 July 1514":"9 juillet 1514","15 November 1509":"15 novembre 1509","1481":"1481","13 November 1520":"13 novembre 1520","1514":"1514","1558":"1558","1501":"1501","1479":"1479","1500":"1500","1478":"1478","1488":"1488","1521":"1521","1596":"1596","1485":"1485","1527":"1527","1449":"1449","Henley-on-Thames, Oxfordshire, England":"Henley-on-Thames, Oxfordshire, Angleterre","St Helen Bishopsgate, London, England, United Kingdom":"St Helen Bishopsgate, Londres, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, Angleterre","North Mymms, Hertfordshire, England":"North Mymms, Hertfordshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Sir Robert Knollys est né en 1481, à North Mymms, Hertfordshire, Angleterre, fils de Robert Knollys et Elizabeth Troutbeck. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Lettice Peniston. En 1509, à l’âge de 28 ans, sa profession de son indiquée est he continued in the same office under henry viii, and received an annuity of £20, on 15 november 1509, and a grant of upclatford, called rookes manor, in hampshire — part of the confiscated property of sir richard empson — on 10 february 1510/11. . Il est décédé en 1521, à Henley-on-Thames, Oxfordshire, Angleterre, à l’âge de 40 ans, et a été enterré à St Helen Bishopsgate, Londres, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni."},"de":{"1481–1521":"1481–1521","1478–1527":"1478–1527","1479–1501":"1479–1501","1485–1558":"1485–1558","1514–1596":"1514–1596","1449–Male":"1449–Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","9 July 1514":"9. Juli 1514","15 November 1509":"15. November 1509","1481":"1481","13 November 1520":"13. November 1520","1514":"1514","1558":"1558","1501":"1501","1479":"1479","1500":"1500","1478":"1478","1488":"1488","1521":"1521","1596":"1596","1485":"1485","1527":"1527","1449":"1449","Henley-on-Thames, Oxfordshire, England":"Henley-on-Thames, Oxfordshire, England","St Helen Bishopsgate, London, England, United Kingdom":"St Helen Bishopsgate, London, England, United Kingdom","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, England","North Mymms, Hertfordshire, England":"North Mymms, Hertfordshire, England","li